DefaultAzureCredential attempts multiple authentication methods in order: Managed Identity, Visual Studio, Visual Studio Code, Azure CLI, and environment variables. Use it for local development and production with managed identity.

```csharp
using Azure.Identity;

var credential = new DefaultAzureCredential();
var token = await credential.GetTokenAsync(new TokenRequestContext(new[] { "https://vault.azure.net/.default" }));
```
